    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Close Finance Periods\n Reopen a Finance Period\n Managing Finance Period Errors\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nClosing and Reopening Finance Periods\n\nFinance departments close accounting and revenue finance periods at the end of each accounting period. After a period closes, the finance department can prepare statements and users can review their financial status. Finance periods need to close at least once a year, though most businesses close them monthly for easier bank statement reconciliation, sales tax report submission, and paying and sending out invoices. Salesforce Billing allows for convenient creation, management, and closing of your business’s finance periods.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce Billing Editions\nClose Finance Periods\nClosing the finance periods makes it easier to reconcile bank statements, submit sales tax reports, pay invoices, and send out invoices.\nReopen a Finance Period\nWhen an order requires an amendment in a closed finance period, reopen the period to make your changes.\nManaging Finance Period Errors\nIf Salesforce Billing encounters validation errors while closing or reopening a finance period, we show error logs with detailed information on why each error happened. You can access the logs on the finance period and on each of its revenue transactions where an occurred. Review the logs to determine what corrective action to take to close or reopen your finance period.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
